{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1781081959087,"sessionID":"ses_14f3ef063ffeCcnT1C938V1BoI","part":{"id":"prt_eb0c1eaa9001gtharapcDCbkfb","messageID":"msg_eb0c1e2fd001a85VBJcLRTA7wE","sessionID":"ses_14f3ef063ffeCcnT1C938V1BoI","snapshot":"4b825dc642cb6eb9a060e54bf8d69288fbee4904","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781081960020,"sessionID":"ses_14f3ef063ffeCcnT1C938V1BoI","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_01DXbjLWNufTEk187iALrDGs","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/dheeraj/Downloads/refactor/bespoke-labs-tasks-01/rust-ls-core/instruction.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/dheeraj/Downloads/refactor/bespoke-labs-tasks-01/rust-ls-core/instruction.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Rust `ls` — Core (Listing + Long Format + Sorting)\n2: \n3: ## Task\n4: \n5: Build an **`ls` command clone** in Rust that reproduces GNU coreutils `ls`\n6: across its three foundational behaviors: **basic listing, long format, and\n7: sorting**. Your implementation must be a standalone binary located at\n8: `/app/workspace/rls`. It will be invoked as:\n9: \n10: ```\n11: /app/workspace/rls [OPTIONS] [FILE]...\n12: ```\n13: \n14: For the same inputs, flags, and environment variables, it must produce the same\n15: output as GNU `ls`. This is a **milestone** task combining the three core tiers; columns, color,\n16: quoting, recursion, and time/size formatting are not the focus here.\n17: \n18: ## Required Flags\n19: \n20: You must support the following flags. Behavior must match GNU coreutils `ls`\n21: exactly.\n22: \n23: ### Listing & filtering\n24: \n25: | Flag | Description |\n26: |------|-------------|\n27: | `-1` | One entry per line |\n28: | `-a`, `--all` | Show entries starting with `.` (incl. `.` and `..`) |\n29: | `-A`, `--almost-all` | Like `-a` but omit `.` and `..` |\n30: \n31: ### Long format\n32: \n33: | Flag | Description |\n34: |------|-------------|\n35: | `-l` | Long listing format |\n36: | `-g` | Like `-l` but omit the owner column |\n37: | `-o` | Like `-l` but omit the group column |\n38: | `-G`, `--no-group` | In long format, omit the group column |\n39: | `-n`, `--numeric-uid-gid` | Long format with numeric UID/GID |\n40: | `-i`, `--inode` | Print inode number |\n41: | `-s`, `--size` | Print allocated size in blocks |\n42: | `--author` | Print the author column (with `-l`) |\n43: | `-L`, `--dereference` | Show info for a symlink's target, not the link itself |\n44: \n45: ### Sorting\n46: \n47: | Flag | Description |\n48: |------|-------------|\n49: | `-S` | Sort by size, largest first |\n50: | `-t` | Sort by modification time, newest first |\n51: | `-r`, `--reverse` | Reverse the sort order |\n52: | `-U` | Do not sort — directory order |\n53: | `-v` | Natural / version sort |\n54: | `-X` | Sort by extension |\n55: | `-f` | Do not sort; enables `-a`, disables `-l` |\n56: | `--sort=WORD` | `none`/`size`/`time`/`version`/`extension` |\n57: | `--group-directories-first` | List directories before files |\n58: \n59: ## Environment Variables\n60: \n61: | Variable | Usage |\n62: |----------|-------|\n63: | `LC_ALL` | Always set to `C` — affects sort order |\n64: | `COLUMNS` | Output width (set to `80`) |\n65: | `TZ` | Timezone (`UTC`) — affects long-format dates and time sorts |\n66: | `TERM` | Terminal type (`xterm-256color`) |\n67: \n68: ## Output Behavior\n69: \n70: - **Default**: name-sorted (`LC_ALL=C`), one entry per line (stdout is not a\n71:   terminal during testing).\n72: - **Long format (`-l`)**: `total <blocks>` header, then\n73:   `<perms> <nlinks> <owner> <group> <size> <date> <name>` with right-aligned\n74:   numeric columns; permission   string includes type char and setuid/setgid/\n75:   sticky bits; recent files show `Mon DD HH:MM`, older files `Mon DD  YYYY`;\n76:   symlinks show `name -> target` (or, under `-L`, the target's own info).\n77:   `-g`/`-o`/`-G` drop a column; `-n` numeric IDs; `-i`/`-s` prepend\n78:   inode/blocks.\n79: - **Sorting**: the sort flags change the primary key; ties fall back to the\n80:   byte-order name sort; `-r` reverses; `-U`/`-f` disable sorting.\n81: - **Exit code**: 0 on success, non-zero on error.\n82: \n83: ## Evaluation\n84: \n85: Your output is compared against GNU `ls` run on the same inputs, flags, and\n86: environment (after trailing-whitespace normalization on each line); it must\n87: match exactly. Aim for faithful, broad coverage of all three areas — basic\n88: listing, long format, and sorting — rather than perfecting one and skipping the\n89: others.\n90: \n91: ## Time Limit\n92: \n93: You have **2 hours** (7200 seconds). Get a compiling one-per-line listing early,\n94: then build the long-format columns, then the sort keys. When ~10 minutes remain,\n95: run a final `cargo build --release`, copy the binary to `/app/workspace/rls`,\n96: and make sure it runs without crashing.\n97: \n98: ## Constraints\n99: \n100: - You must implement this in **Rust**.\n101: - You may **not** use the `uutils` crate or any crate that provides a\n102:   ready-made `ls` implementation.\n103: - You may use standard library crates and general-purpose crates (e.g. `libc`,\n104:   `nix`, `clap`).\n105: - Your final binary must be at `/app/workspace/rls`.\n106: - The system `ls` command is disabled — do not attempt to call it.\n107: - Each test has a per-case timeout (10 seconds).\n108: \n109: ## Getting Started\n110: \n111: Example fixtures are in `/app/workspace/examples/`:\n112: \n113: ```bash\n114: diff <(/app/workspace/rls -l /app/workspace/examples/basic) \\\n115:      /app/workspace/examples/expected/t2_basic_long.txt\n116: ```\n117: \n118: Test fixtures are in `/app/fixtures/` and test definitions in `/app/tests/`.\n119: \n120: ## Tips\n121: \n122: - Both your binary and the oracle run on the same filesystem, so inode/owner/\n123:   group/size/nlinks/block columns match when read with `stat`/`lstat`.\n124: - `LC_ALL=C` means ASCII byte-order sorting (uppercase before lowercase).\n125: - **Version sort (`-v`)** compares digit runs numerically and other runs\n126:   byte-wise (`file2` < `file10`).\n127: - All fixture timestamps are fixed past dates, so the recent-vs-old date format\n128:   switch is deterministic.\n\n(End of file - total 128 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Rust `ls` — Core (Listing + Long Format + Sorting)\n\n## Task\n\nBuild an **`ls` command clone** in Rust that reproduces GNU coreutils `ls`\nacross its three foundational behaviors: **basic listing, long format, and\nsorting**. Your implementation must be a standalone binary located at\n`/app/workspace/rls`. It will be invoked as:\n\n```\n/app/workspace/rls [OPTIONS] [FILE]...\n```\n\nFor the same inputs, flags, and environment variables, it must produce the same\noutput as GNU `ls`. This is a **milestone** task combining the three core tiers; columns, color,\nquoting, recursion, and time/size formatting are not the focus here.\n\n## Required Flags\n\nYou must support the following flags. Behavior must match GNU coreutils `ls`","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/dheeraj/Downloads/refactor/bespoke-labs-tasks-01/rust-ls-core/instruction.md","text":"# Rust `ls` — Core (Listing + Long Format + Sorting)\n\n## Task\n\nBuild an **`ls` command clone** in Rust that reproduces GNU coreutils `ls`\nacross its three foundational behaviors: **basic listing, long format, and\nsorting**. Your implementation must be a standalone binary located at\n`/app/workspace/rls`. It will be invoked as:\n\n```\n/app/workspace/rls [OPTIONS] [FILE]...\n```\n\nFor the same inputs, flags, and environment variables, it must produce the same\noutput as GNU `ls`. This is a **milestone** task combining the three core tiers; columns, color,\nquoting, recursion, and time/size formatting are not the focus here.\n\n## Required Flags\n\nYou must support the following flags. Behavior must match GNU coreutils `ls`\nexactly.\n\n### Listing & filtering\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `-1` | One entry per line |\n| `-a`, `--all` | Show entries starting with `.` (incl. `.` and `..`) |\n| `-A`, `--almost-all` | Like `-a` but omit `.` and `..` |\n\n### Long format\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `-l` | Long listing format |\n| `-g` | Like `-l` but omit the owner column |\n| `-o` | Like `-l` but omit the group column |\n| `-G`, `--no-group` | In long format, omit the group column |\n| `-n`, `--numeric-uid-gid` | Long format with numeric UID/GID |\n| `-i`, `--inode` | Print inode number |\n| `-s`, `--size` | Print allocated size in blocks |\n| `--author` | Print the author column (with `-l`) |\n| `-L`, `--dereference` | Show info for a symlink's target, not the link itself |\n\n### Sorting\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `-S` | Sort by size, largest first |\n| `-t` | Sort by modification time, newest first |\n| `-r`, `--reverse` | Reverse the sort order |\n| `-U` | Do not sort — directory order |\n| `-v` | Natural / version sort |\n| `-X` | Sort by extension |\n| `-f` | Do not sort; enables `-a`, disables `-l` |\n| `--sort=WORD` | `none`/`size`/`time`/`version`/`extension` |\n| `--group-directories-first` | List directories before files |\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| `LC_ALL` | Always set to `C` — affects sort order |\n| `COLUMNS` | Output width (set to `80`) |\n| `TZ` | Timezone (`UTC`) — affects long-format dates and time sorts |\n| `TERM` | Terminal type (`xterm-256color`) |\n\n## Output Behavior\n\n- **Default**: name-sorted (`LC_ALL=C`), one entry per line (stdout is not a\n  terminal during testing).\n- **Long format (`-l`)**: `total <blocks>` header, then\n  `<perms> <nlinks> <owner> <group> <size> <date> <name>` with right-aligned\n  numeric columns; permission   string includes type char and setuid/setgid/\n  sticky bits; recent files show `Mon DD HH:MM`, older files `Mon DD  YYYY`;\n  symlinks show `name -> target` (or, under `-L`, the target's own info).\n  `-g`/`-o`/`-G` drop a column; `-n` numeric IDs; `-i`/`-s` prepend\n  inode/blocks.\n- **Sorting**: the sort flags change the primary key; ties fall back to the\n  byte-order name sort; `-r` reverses; `-U`/`-f` disable sorting.\n- **Exit code**: 0 on success, non-zero on error.\n\n## Evaluation\n\nYour output is compared against GNU `ls` run on the same inputs, flags, and\nenvironment (after trailing-whitespace normalization on each line); it must\nmatch exactly. Aim for faithful, broad coverage of all three areas — basic\nlisting, long format, and sorting — rather than perfecting one and skipping the\nothers.\n\n## Time Limit\n\nYou have **2 hours** (7200 seconds). Get a compiling one-per-line listing early,\nthen build the long-format columns, then the sort keys. When ~10 minutes remain,\nrun a final `cargo build --release`, copy the binary to `/app/workspace/rls`,\nand make sure it runs without crashing.\n\n## Constraints\n\n- You must implement this in **Rust**.\n- You may **not** use the `uutils` crate or any crate that provides a\n  ready-made `ls` implementation.\n- You may use standard library crates and general-purpose crates (e.g. `libc`,\n  `nix`, `clap`).\n- Your final binary must be at `/app/workspace/rls`.\n- The system `ls` command is disabled — do not attempt to call it.\n- Each test has a per-case timeout (10 seconds).\n\n## Getting Started\n\nExample fixtures are in `/app/workspace/examples/`:\n\n```bash\ndiff <(/app/workspace/rls -l /app/workspace/examples/basic) \\\n     /app/workspace/examples/expected/t2_basic_long.txt\n```\n\nTest fixtures are in `/app/fixtures/` and test definitions in `/app/tests/`.\n\n## Tips\n\n- Both your binary and the oracle run on the same filesystem, so inode/owner/\n  group/size/nlinks/block columns match when read with `stat`/`lstat`.\n- `LC_ALL=C` means ASCII byte-order sorting (uppercase before lowercase).\n- **Version sort (`-v`)** compares digit runs numerically and other runs\n  byte-wise (`file2` < `file10`).\n- All fixture timestamps are fixed past dates, so the recent-vs-old date format\n  switch is deterministic.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":128,"totalLines":128,"truncated":false}},"title":"rust-ls-core/instruction.md","time":{"start":1781081959991,"end":1781081960016}},"metadata":{"anthropic":{"caller":{"type":"direct"}}},"id":"prt_eb0c1eaac001obUEUvqsQvIwB1","sessionID":"ses_14f3ef063ffeCcnT1C938V1BoI","messageID":"msg_eb0c1e2fd001a85VBJcLRTA7wE"}}
