{"type":"text","timestamp":1781081987041,"sessionID":"ses_14f3ef063ffeCcnT1C938V1BoI","part":{"id":"prt_eb0c24034001CDTAm4qEc2R0ol","messageID":"msg_eb0c23784001B7Hux2r7BjahrV","sessionID":"ses_14f3ef063ffeCcnT1C938V1BoI","type":"text","text":"Confirmed: `bc` is no longer used (scoring was moved to Python `compute_reward.py`). Comment in Dockerfile says \"verifier helpers (openssl/bc/file)\" but bc is unused.\n\nNo `.dockerignore` — fine but workspace is tiny.\n\n**Solution clean:** Only `solve.sh` — clean.\n\n**test.sh:** Locks /logs/verifier (mandatory), locks /tests (good - Harbor upload resets perms), env scrub, pre-kill agent processes, decrypt oracle, build under strace as agent (necessary - build.rs runs agent code), strace tripwires on build + run, static anti-cheat greps (these are belt-and-suspenders since strace + binary hash check exist; but they're cheap and orthogonal). The `find /tests -type f -name '*.sh' -exec chmod +x` — but there are no other .sh in /tests (only test.sh + .py). So this is unnecessary, comment says \"Restore exec bits on helper scripts\" but there are no helper .sh.","time":{"start":1781081980980,"end":1781081987035}}}
